            <abstract id="ref11" label="Abstract">These materials are comprised of grammars, glossaries, and books of prayers and hymns, in various Native American languages. Includes Huron, Mohawk, miscellaneous Iroquoian languages; Abenaki, Algonquin, Montagnais, Micmac, Ottawa; Slave, and unidentified Northwest Coast languages. Most were written by Jesuit missionaries before 1760. Also included is a register of Indian baptisms and marriages, and a brief history of the Huron Indians.</abstract>
            <langmaterial id="ref16" label="Language of Materials note">The collection is in Iroquois, Huron, and Algonquin languages.</langmaterial>
